Class OneBoxProvider

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig
public abstract class OneBoxProvider
extends javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet

Abstract base class servlet for providing OneBox results.

Services GET method requests from OneBox clients by unpacking their request parameters and delegating to one of the overloaded provideOneBoxResults() methods depending on the authType parameter.

Providers need to extend this class and override one or more of its provideOneBoxResults methods. The base class implementation of those methods will all throw UnsupportedOperationException.

See Also:
OneBoxResults, Serialized Form

processRequest

protected void processRequest(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                              javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
                       throws javax.servlet.ServletException,
                              java.io.IOException
Top level request processor for this OneBox provider.

Unpacks the HTTP request's parameters and passes them into one of the provideOneBoxResults methods, based on the value of the authType parameter, for further processing.

Returns an HTTP response with XML that adhere's to the Google DTD defining the schema for OneBox for Enterprise provider results.

Throws:
javax.servlet.ServletException
java.io.IOException

Method to handle OneBox requests where no user authentication is required.

Parameters:
apiMaj - the OneBox for Enterprise API major version
apiMin - the OneBox for Enterprise API minor version
oneboxName - the name of the OneBox module
dateTime - the date and time of the OneBox query
ipAddr - the IP address of the end user as determined by the OneBox client
lang - the language of the user's browser, two character language code
query - the end user's query, UTF-8 encoded and URL-escaped
matchGroups - reqular expression evaluation match groups
